The paper focuses on a new large-scale dataset for autonomous driving research, which includes LiDAR and camera data, as well as annotations for 2D and 3D bounding boxes. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques for detection and tracking tasks, indicating that it may also be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions the use of natural language processing techniques for providing information about the dataset, suggesting that it may also be relevant to the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
